<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        WINDSHIELD GLASS - WINDSHIELD INSTALL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>WINDSHIELD INSTALL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If weatherseal was removed:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position center (vertical) portion of weatherseal into the divider bar (
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_19.xml" xrefid="f1600622">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install weatherseal to perimeter of mounting fence.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a bead of sealer around the entire perimeter of the weatherseal between the seal and
                the mounting fence. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16006_20.xml" xrefid="hl1600610">WINDSHIELD SEALING
                    <xref refid="hl1600610"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a soapy solution or rubber lubricant to glass channel in weatherseal, and position
                windshield halves into the weatherseal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Work the locking strip into the groove around the entire weatherseal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the center locking strip (Item 1,
                <hotlnk document="s16006_19.xml" xrefid="f1600622">Figure 22</hotlnk>) into the center section of the
                weatherseal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the wiper arms to the wiper motor shafts and install the windshield washer hoses to
                the appropriate fittings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean all excess sealer from the work area.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
